  <name>TuxFlow</name>
  <summary>Linux-native dev environment manager</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      TuxFlow lets developers manage their entire dev environment from one window —
      start/stop/restart dev servers, run multiple AI coding agents side by side,
      monitor process status and resource usage, auto-restart crashed processes,
      watch files for changes, and expose an MCP server so AI agents can observe
      and control neighboring processes.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Manage multiple dev processes (servers, watchers, queues) from a single window</li>
      <li>Run AI coding agents (Claude Code, Codex, Gemini CLI) side by side</li>
      <li>Auto-detect project stacks (Node.js, Rust, Python, Go, PHP, Ruby, Docker)</li>
      <li>Auto-restart crashed processes with exponential backoff</li>
      <li>File watching with glob patterns to restart on changes</li>
      <li>Command palette (Ctrl+K) for quick navigation</li>
      <li>MCP server for AI agent integration</li>
      <li>TOML-based configuration</li>
      <li>Dark-first design with GTK4 + libadwaita</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
